class="SongDescription__Content-sc-615rvk-2 kRzyD"><div class="RichText__Container-oz284w-0 iGfiAx"><p>“Murdergram Deux” marks LL Cool J and Eminem’s highly anticipated first collaboration and the fourth single from LL Cool J’s long-awaited upcoming album, <em>The FORCE</em>. With LL’s nostalgic bravado and Eminem’s signature speedy flow and subtle wordplay, the song sees the pair boasting about their raw “unapologetic” style and credibility in the rap game. The track – a sequel to LL’s <a href="https://genius.com/Ll-cool-j-murdergram-lyrics" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/songs/29043">original “Murdergram”</a> – is produced by Eminem and Q-Tip, LL’s fellow Queens rap legend and former member of <a href="https://genius.com/artists/A-tribe-called-quest" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/artists/519">A Tribe Called Quest</a>, who has produced the entire album.</p>

<p>Two months before the official release of the song, an unfinished version of “Murdergram Deux” was leaked to the public, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2sl8rkiKLxc" rel="noopener nofollow">visibly annoying LL</a>. The song was officially released on August 30th as the album’s fourth single, which is set to drop on September 9, 2024.</p></div></div></div><div class="ExpandableContent__ButtonContainer-sc-1165iv-3 class="SongDescription__Content-sc-615rvk-2 kRzyD"><div class="RichText__Container-oz284w-0 iGfiAx"><p>“Murdergram Deux” marks LL Cool J and Eminem’s highly anticipated first collaboration and the fourth single from LL Cool J’s long-awaited upcoming album, <em>The FORCE</em>. With LL’s nostalgic bravado and Eminem’s signature speedy flow and subtle wordplay, the song sees the pair boasting about their raw “unapologetic” style and credibility in the rap game. The track – a sequel to LL’s <a href="https://genius.com/Ll-cool-j-murdergram-lyrics" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/songs/29043">original “Murdergram”</a> – is produced by Eminem and Q-Tip, LL’s fellow Queens rap legend and former member of <a href="https://genius.com/artists/A-tribe-called-quest" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/artists/519">A Tribe Called Quest</a>, who has produced the entire album.</p>

<p>Two months before the official release of the song, an unfinished version of “Murdergram Deux” was leaked to the public, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2sl8rkiKLxc" rel="noopener nofollow">visibly annoying LL</a>. The song was officially released on August 30th as the album’s fourth single, which is set to drop on September 9, 2024.</p></div></div></div><div class="ExpandableContent__ButtonContainer-sc-1165iv-3 I can't understand a single word you're saying I think you have syrup brain 'Bout to finish you like polyurethane ( Huh ) All that molly probably sure to drain your spinal fluid from your vertebrae This the Murdergram and I brought my murder game My shit fire, that is why you log on it like Duraflame But as far as boulevards, I'm talking 'bout Farmers like insurance claims (Pff) I just blew your girl away, but she on so much blow and lean (What?) (Kane), the king, and they feed me grapes (Yeah) Either way, I got more on my plate than an all you can eat buffet (Woo) So better pick a B.C. date 'cause your history is shady (Yeah, set ) As they 'bout to set it on you like a TV tray (Haha, yup) Man, I see the way people say I'm so evil (What?) They fuckin' think that Timothy McVeigh and my DNA are exactly the same But when I leave this game (Nope) Things just ain't gonna be the same (Nah) But it's in need of change (Yeah), and I'm the meter maid (Haha) Go ahead and crack a bottle, 'cause this is E and J Meaning me and James (Yeah) Got that avocado and we the sociopaths And we got your ho on our laps And we're goin' back to Cali so she can blow on our sax [Outro: Eminem & LL COOL J ] Brang-brang, brr-brr-brr-brrr, brr-brring I don't think so 1 Embed Cancel How to Format Lyrics: Type out all lyrics, even repeating song parts like the chorus Lyrics should be broken down into individual lines Use section headers above different song parts like [Verse], [Chorus], etc. Use italics ( lyric ) and bold ( lyric ) to distinguish between different vocalists in the same song part If you don’t understand a lyric, use [?] To learn more, check out our transcription guide or visit our transcribers forum About Genius Annotation 4 contributors “Murdergram Deux” marks LL Cool J and Eminem’s highly anticipated first collaboration and the fourth single from LL Cool J’s long-awaited upcoming album, The FORCE . With LL’s nostalgic bravado and Eminem’s signature speedy flow and subtle wordplay, the song sees the pair boasting about their raw “unapologetic” style and credibility in the rap game. The track – a sequel to LL’s original “Murdergram” – is produced by Eminem and Q-Tip, LL’s fellow Queens rap legend and former member of A Tribe Called Quest , who has produced the entire album. Two months before the official release of the song, an unfinished version of “Murdergram Deux” was leaked to the public, visibly annoying LL . The song was officially released on August 30th as the album’s fourth single, which is set to drop on September 9, 2024. Genius Answer 1 contributor The two hip-hop giants have never collaborated on a track before despite countlessly praising one another on social media. Eminem grew up listening to LL, naming him as one of his idols and inspirations . “Murdergram Deux” marks the first track which LL Cool J and Eminem will share. With LL’s nostalgic bravado and Eminem’s signature speedy flow and subtle wordplay, the song sees the pair boasting about their raw “unapologetic” style and credibility in the rap game. The track – a sequel to LL’s original “Murdergram” – is produced by Eminem and Q-Tip, LL’s fellow Queens rap legend and former member of A Tribe Called Quest , who has produced the entire album. Two months before the official release of the song, an unfinished version of “Murdergram Deux” was leaked to the public, visibly annoying LL . The song was officially released on August 30th as the album’s fourth single, which is set to drop on September 9, 2024. Genius Answer 1 contributor The two hip-hop giants have never collaborated on a track before despite countlessly praising one another on social media. Eminem grew up listening to LL, naming him as one of his idols and inspirations . “Murdergram Deux” marks the first track which LL Cool J and Eminem will share. transcribers forum transcription guide transcribers forum About Genius Annotation 4 contributors “Murdergram Deux” marks LL Cool J and Eminem’s highly anticipated first collaboration and the fourth single from LL Cool J’s long-awaited upcoming album, The FORCE . With LL’s nostalgic bravado and Eminem’s signature speedy flow and subtle wordplay, the song sees the pair boasting about their raw “unapologetic” style and credibility in the rap game. The track – a sequel to LL’s original “Murdergram” – is produced by Eminem and Q-Tip, LL’s fellow Queens rap legend and former member of A Tribe Called Quest , who has produced the entire album. Two months before the official release of the song, an unfinished version of “Murdergram Deux” was leaked to the public, visibly annoying LL . The song was officially released on August 30th as the album’s fourth single, which is set to drop on September 9, 2024. Genius Answer 1 contributor The two hip-hop giants have never collaborated on a track before despite countlessly praising one another on social media. Eminem grew up listening to LL, naming him as one of his idols and inspirations . “Murdergram Deux” marks the first track which LL Cool J and Eminem will share. The track – a sequel to LL’s original “Murdergram” – is produced by Eminem and Q-Tip, LL’s fellow Queens rap legend and former member of A Tribe Called Quest , who has produced the entire album. The song was officially released on August 30th as the album’s fourth single, which is set to drop on September 9, 2024.
